The journalist writes an essay about a family in which there has not been a single quarrel in fifty years. Interviews a woman:
- How did you manage to live for so many years in a world of mutual understanding and harmony?
The woman answers:
- After the wedding, my husband put me on a cart and we went to his farm. While we were riding, the horse stumbled and my husband said - ONE!
- After a while, the horse stumbled again and the husband said - TWO!
- Just before the farm, the horse stumbled again and the husband said - THREE!
- Then he took out a shotgun and shot this horse.
- I couldn't look at it calmly, I felt very sorry for the poor animal, I started shouting at my husband...
Journalist:
- And what's next?
Woman:
- The husband said - ONCE!
